definition: A local interbreeding group of organisms within a species. In salmon, a deme typically corresponds to a spawning population at a specific site. Demes are the finest biological unit and make up populations.
Relates a deme to the population it belongs to.
Relates a population to one of its constituent demes.
Individuals that were born or reared in a hatchery facility.
definition_source: DFO. (2018). Review of genetically based targets for enhanced contributions to Canadian Pacific Chinook Salmon populations. DFO Can. Sci. Advis. Sec. Sci. Advis. Rep. 2018/001. (Erratum: October 2023)
definition_source_text: DFO. (2018). Review of genetically based targets for enhanced contributions to Canadian Pacific Chinook Salmon populations. DFO Can. Sci. Advis. Sec. Sci. Advis. Rep. 2018/001. (Erratum: October 2023)

definition: Individuals that are born and reared in the wild (natural environment).
definition_source: DFO. (2018). Review of genetically based targets for enhanced contributions to Canadian Pacific Chinook Salmon populations. DFO Can. Sci. Advis. Sec. Sci. Advis. Rep. 2018/001. (Erratum: October 2023)
definition_source_text: DFO. (2018). Review of genetically based targets for enhanced contributions to Canadian Pacific Chinook Salmon populations. DFO Can. Sci. Advis. Sec. Sci. Advis. Rep. 2018/001. (Erratum: October 2023)

definition: A group of organisms of the same species occupying a defined area that interbreed and share a gene pool. In salmon, populations are composed of one or more demes and form the biological basis for Conservation Units.
Controlled vocabulary for describing the origin of individual salmon (e.g., natural-origin, hatchery-origin, mixed-origin).
